  "prompt": "What do you say to the man you love when it's over?",
  "response": "When facing the end of a relationship with someone you love, it's important to approach the conversation with honesty, compassion, and respect. Here's a suggestion for what you might say:\n\n\"I care about you deeply, and this is very difficult for me. We've shared so many meaningful moments together, but I feel that we've grown apart in ways that can't be bridged. I believe that ending our relationship is the best decision for both of us to find happiness. This isn't easy for me, and I know it won't be for you either. I want you to know that I'll always cherish the time we've had together and wish nothing but the best for you.\"\n\nTailor your words to fit the unique circumstances and emotions involved in your relationship.",
